programme.title: Live US Open Golf
programme.desc: The opening day's play in the year's second Major from Shinnecock Hills in Suffolk County, New York, which will begin with America's Brooks Koepka as the reigning champion. Rickie Fowler ended day one in the lead last year in Wisconsin tying the US Open record for lowest first-round score in relation to par with a seven-under 65, but Paul Casey and Xander Schauffele were just one stroke behind, with Koepka, Tommy Fleetwood and Brian Harman a further shot adrift.

programme.title: Live US Open Golf
programme.desc: The second day's play from Shinnecock Hills in Suffolk County, New York, where the players will hope to make the cut and progress to the weekend's rounds. For the first time in a Major since the introduction of the Official World Golf Ranking in 1986, the world's top three in Dustin Johnson, Rory McIlroy, and Jason Day all missed the cut last year. At the other end of the leaderboard, England's Paul Casey and Tommy Fleetwood shared the lead with Brian Harman and Brooks Koepka.

We look back at Borussia Monchengladbach's Bundesliga clash with Hoffenheim. A Hoffenheim win would've lifted them back into the top six for the first time since December.(n)
We revisit Der Klassiker as Bayern Munich hoped to clinch their sixth consecutive Bundesliga title against Borussia Dortmund. Peter Stoger's men had gone 12 league games unbeaten.(n)
We look back at April's dramatic Bundesliga clash between Schalke and Hamburg at the Volksparkstadion. The hosts were looking to register their first league win since November.(n)
We revisit the do-or-die clash between Cologne and Freiburg, with Cologne needing a win to stay in the Bundesliga. Freiburg secured a dramatic 4-3 victory when the two last met.(n)
We revisit the Bundesliga clash between Hertha Berlin and RB Leipzig at the Olympiastadion. Hertha still had hopes of a top four finish providing other results went their way.(n)
